g
\in L^1(\mathbb{R^n})
\operatorname{dom}\left(f*g\right)
\left\|f*g\right\|_{L^{1}} \le \left\|f\right\|_{L^1} \left\|g\right\|_{L^1}
\|f*g\|_{L^1}
\left\|f*g\right\|_{L^{1}}=\int_{R^n}|\int_{R^n}f(x-y)g(y)dy|dx \le \int_{R^n}\int_{R^n}|f(x-y)g(y)|dydx = 
\int_{R^n}|g(y)|\int_{R^n}|f(x-y)|dxdy=\int_{R^n}|g(y)|\int_{R^n}|f(t)|dtdy = \left\|g\right\|_{L^{1}} \left\|f\right\|_{L^{1}}
L^{1}(\mathbb{R}^{n})
[L^{1}(\mathbb{R}^{n}),*]
K
K(x) \in L^{1}(\mathbb{R}^{n})
 f \rightarrow K*f
L^{1}(\mathbb{R}^{n})
 \leq \left\Vert K \right\Vert_{L^{1}}
\left\Vert K*f \right\Vert_{L^{1}} \leq \left\Vert K \right\Vert_{L^{1}}\left\Vert f \right\Vert_{L^{1}}
